03/09/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The country is observing a day of mourning Monday (September 3rd) for seven firefighters killed as they battled blazes on Kornati islands last week. If arson caused the fires, Prime Minister Ivo Sanader vowed to find those responsible and punish them. He is attending a ceremony in the firefighters' hometown, Sibenik. Ten other firefighters were trapped by the flames. Four remain in critical condition. (Vjesnik, Vecernji List, Javno.hr - 03/09/07; UPI, AFP - 01/09/07)
